\begin{pa} \label{PA:7.4}
  \ba
\item Suppose you have a bank account in which money grows at an
  annual rate of 3\%.
  \begin{itemize}
    \item If you have \$10,000 in the account, at what rate is your
      money growing?
    \item Suppose that you are also withdrawing money from the account
      at \$1,000 per year.  What is the rate of change in the amount
      of money in the account?
  \end{itemize}
\item Suppose that a water tank holds 100 gallons and that a salty
  solution, which contains 20 grams of salt in every gallon, enters the
  tank at 2 gallons per minute.   
  \begin{itemize}
    \item How much salt enters the tank each minute?
    \item Suppose that there are 300 grams of salt in the tank.  How
      much salt is in each gallon?
    \item Finally, suppose that water is pumped out of the tank at the
      rate of 2 gallons per minute.  How much salt leaves the tank
      each minute?
    \item What is the total rate of change in the amount of salt in
      the tank?
  \end{itemize}
\ea
\end{pa} 
\afterpa
